baseline: An international conference to inform, train and engage the interest of all education stakeholders in the digital challenges.
---
monday:  Monday August 27, 2018 in [Bozar](https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/3299877), teachers, directorates and the general public will be able to follow conferences, a round-table, an interactive show to apprehend this new world makes digital, its challenges and opportunities. During the breaks, they will be able to meet a large number of actors, mainly associations, who offer activities related to digital and training. Childcare solutions with activities will be organized so that all parents can participate.
---
thuesday: Tuesday 28 August at [ESI](https://www.openstreetmap.org/node/2339843466) and at [ISIB](https://www.openstreetmap.org/relation/7259430), teachers will be invited to many practical workshops during which they will be the learners, so as to find their alter-egos, develop with them content and experiences to reuse in class what they have learned. These hands-on workshops will focus on a wide variety of topics around education and the use of digital and computer thinking, and new ways of working that are digital.
---
